                <li><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">LumeoPresetOptions</code> — single source of truth for option arrays (indexes are the stored values — append-only).</li>
                <li><strong>/themes customizer:</strong> live 6-char preset code with copy button — puts <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">lumeo theme apply --preset &lt;code&gt;</code> on the clipboard.</li>
                <li><strong>CLI:</strong> new <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">lumeo theme apply --preset &lt;code&gt;</code> subcommand. Decodes the code and prints the resolved configuration + a ready-to-paste JS snippet that drives the runtime theme-switcher. <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--dry-run</code> flag.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
